Learnt a whole lot...let me share with you😆
--------
•Do not make a decision to be in a relationship based on excitement. Let the excitement settle
•Do not make vital decisions out of sadness, rejection, fear or when you are angry.
There's no human being that is capable of fixing rejection/depression/sadness. Only God can fix it!
•Physical attraction is key, go for someone you 're physically attracted to😉
•Ask about the friendships of your patner,you should know how well they manage friendships.
To enter a relationship with someone that has no friends already tells of their character.
Ask how long they've been friends.
•You don't find good friends, you build good friendships.

Healthy friendships are building blocks for healthy marital relationships.
---------
The CHURCH has a pivotal role to play in relationships.
But, •The Church must not tell you WHO to marry.
•The Church must not tell you NOT to marry
•The Church must MAKE you accountable about Who and How you marry.
----------
God only GUIDES you on who to marry; He can't choose for you. 
You make your choice but your choice should be guided by God's word.
1 COrinthians 7 vs 39
